! Configuration

All ProseMirror settings are available under ''Control Panel > Settings > ProseMirror''.

!! Markdown Shortcuts

When enabled, the editor recognises Markdown-style shortcuts:

* `**bold**` → ''bold''
* `*italic*` → //italic//
* `~~strike~~` → ~~strike~~
* <code>``code``</code> → `code`
* `# Heading` → heading
* `---` → horizontal rule
* <code>```</code> → code block

Output is always WikiText. Config tiddler: `$:/config/prosemirror/markdown-shortcuts`.

!! Widget Blocks

Visual rendering of `<<macro>>` syntax can be toggled via `$:/config/prosemirror/enable-widget-blocks`.

!! Autocomplete Triggers

The characters that open the autocomplete dropdown are configurable:

|!Type |!Default triggers |!Config tiddler |
|Links |`[[` `【【` |`$:/config/prosemirror/autocomplete/link-triggers` |
|Macros |`<<` `《《` |`$:/config/prosemirror/autocomplete/macro-triggers` |
|Transclusions |`{{` `「『` |`$:/config/prosemirror/autocomplete/transclusion-triggers` |

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

Each toolbar action has a configurable shortcut via its EditorAction tiddler. Set the `keyboard-shortcut` field, or use `none` to disable.

|!Action |!Default |
|Bold |Mod-b |
|Italic |Mod-i |
|Heading 1–3 |Shift-Ctrl-1 to 3 |
|Blockquote |Ctrl-> |
|Code block |Shift-Ctrl-\\ |
|Horizontal rule |Mod-_ |
